			<ns0:name>esei...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/118329321683865945653/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We encountered this bug because Chromium's base/lock_impl_posix.cc uses PTHREAD_MUTEX_ERRORCHECK in Debug builds and asserts if the return code from pthread_mutex_unlock is not 0.

Took me a long time to find this bug, but it's clearly a bug in the interaction between cond_wait and the pthread_mutex_t.  I'll see if I can make a patch to nc_condvar.c which fixes the issue.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-11-16T00:12:32.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-11-16T00:12:32.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by esei...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1177#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1177/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>